## §9 — Scenario Q&A (drill)

### 9.1 One-way audio
**Scenario:** 200 OK but one side silent.  
**A:** SDP vs real RTP path; `nft` UDP rules; RTPengine leg config; conntrack / rp_filter.  
**Commands:** Recipes 8.1–8.3, 8.6.

### 9.2 New trunk this week
**A:** Lock auth, codecs, DTMF, CPS, CLI, timers; lab → OPTIONS → test DID → canary → full cut.  
**Commands:** `dig` carrier SRV (8.8); `openssl s_client` for TLS trunk.

### 9.3 Dispatcher all red
**A:** `kamcmd dispatcher.list`; OPTIONS blocked by nft; bind IP wrong after NIC rename — `ip -br addr`.

### 9.4 RTPengine post-kernel upgrade
**A:** Kernel module not rebuilt — rebuild, restart, `journalctl`, one test call.

### 9.5 Asterisk inbound NAT
**A:** PJSIP `externaddr` / `localnet`; often Contact fix belongs in Kamailio for multi-NAT.

### 9.6 TLS Sunday fail
**A:** cert dates / chain / SAN; `openssl x509 -noout -dates`; chrony drift.

### 9.7 Jitter / underwater audio
**A:** RTCP stats; DSCP stripped on a hop; reduce unnecessary transcode; endpoint jitter buffer.

### 9.8 SIPp before peak
**A:** Measure SIP success %, PDD, 5xx, CPU, fds, conntrack — Recipe 8.6.

### 9.9 Grafana minimums
**A:** OPTIONS per trunk, 5xx rate, REGISTER drop, RTPengine errors, node CPU + conntrack.

### 9.10 Twilio/Genesys "lab works, DC fails"
**A:** Egress NAT IP ≠ internal host IP on their allowlist; TLS vs UDP; SNI.

### 9.11 Homer hygiene
**A:** HEP + TTL retention; tcpdump rotation (8.3); filter by Call-ID.

### 9.12 T.38 after upgrade
**A:** re-INVITE path; RTPengine T.38 build; ATA firmware; canary fax DID.

### 9.13 SIP ALG on-site
**A:** sngrep proof of Contact corruption; disable ALG or DMZ to SBC; MOP + rollback.

### 9.14 PostgreSQL CDR slow
**A:** Missing index on `(call_date, src)`; partition by month; vacuum; reporting off replica.

### 9.15 Git drift
**A:** `kamailio -c` in CI; Ansible apply from pipeline; checksum alert on prod file.

